-- Silver Eagle Fined $1 Million After Blast at Refinery, Deseret News Says
-- Samantha Zee
-- 2010-06-22T01:36:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-22/silver-eagle-fined-1-million-after-blast-at-refinery-deseret-news-says.html

          
          
             Silver Eagle Refining Inc. has been
fined more than $1 million by the Utah Occupational Safety and
Health Division over an explosion and a flash fire at its Woods
Cross refinery last year, the Deseret News  reported .  
 Louis Silva, administrator for the Utah OSH, couldn’t
immediately be contacted by telephone, and Cindy Gubler, a
spokeswoman for Silver Eagle, didn’t return an e-mail or
telephone call from Bloomberg News seeking comment.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
 Samantha Zee  in San Francisco at 
 szee@bloomberg.net   
          
          


  


        